	"system": {
		"description": {
			"value": "<p><em>You speak a prayer while sprinkling powdered silver and iron onto a liquid or object. The powder liquifies and then dissipates, imbuing the object with holy power.</em></p><p><strong>Ritual Casting Time:</strong> 1 Minute</p><p><strong>Materials:</strong> You require 0.2 pounds of @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.fnmCUzOkiNZDOpQ0]{pure holy silver and iron powder} (one quarter sterling silver, three quarters iron), typically valued at 25 gold. You can alternatively use a pound of @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.IndrcQ3rdMXvfyVh]{holy water} to sanctify a weapon. This spell consumes this material.</p><p><strong>Enchant Item</strong></p><ul><li><p>You touch a weapon. That weapon counts as a &amp;reference[silver] weapon if it wasn't already.</p></li><li><p>Alternatively, you can bless a pound of water, which becomes @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.IndrcQ3rdMXvfyVh]{holy water}. If you use this spell to create holy water, the duration is permanent.</p></li></ul>",
